                    <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="Type species by original designation">
                        <title>Type species by original designation.</title>
                        <p><italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Hallodapomimus</tp:taxon-name-part> <tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="species">elektrinus</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> Herczek, 2000: 145.</p>
                    </tp:treatment-sec>
                    <tp:treatment-sec sec-type="Diagnosis">
                        <title>Diagnosis.</title>
                        <p>Distinguished from the other extinct hallodapine genus <italic><tp:taxon-name><tp:taxon-name-part taxon-name-part-type="genus">Leptomimoides</tp:taxon-name-part></tp:taxon-name></italic> by a combination of the following characters: smooth, impunctate dorsal surface of body, distinctive coloration (head, pronotum and part of cuneus dark, and clavus partly black), head almost twice as broad as long, pronotum 1.2–1.3 times wider than long; pronotal calli visible.</p>
                    </tp:treatment-sec>
